<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-08T12:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-08T12:29:00-05:00" n="6" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d6">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/8038</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Petrograd</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-08T21:00:00+03:31"><hi rend="italic">December
                                            8, 1917, 9 p.m.</hi></date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received December 11, 12.18
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2073. Afternoon papers state thousand Japanese militia landed
                                Vladivostok from transport convoyed by cruiser <hi rend="italic">Okuma</hi>. Called Japanese Ambassador, read statement to him.
                                He says had no advices and believed report untrue.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_FDR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>